New Records: Jamaica secured their sixth straight win over Honduras in the CONCACAF Nations League competition
Key Match Events: Denil Maldonado scored an own goal in the 49th minute
Michail Antonio scored a penalty in the 76th minute
David Ruiz scored for Honduras in the 50th minute
Pre-Game Insights: The pressure was on Jamaica to deliver the goods in Honduras following the disappointing 0-0 stalemate against Cuba
Jamaica had to win to avoid a bad situation in Group B
Post-Match Reflections: Reggae Boyz head coach Steve McClaren praised his team's bravery and performance
McClaren noted that his team was magnificent, controlling the game and building from the back
He expressed pride in the players' team spirit and ability to come out on top in a tough game
Miscellaneous Highlights: Jamaica made two changes to the starting team, bringing in Greg Leigh for Dexter Lembikisa at right back and replacing Jamal Lowe with Norman Campbell at outside right
Campbell's run led to the first goal, and substitute Kaheim Dixon assisted in Jamaica's second goal
Others: The CONCACAF Nations League competition is ongoing, with Jamaica topping Group B with four points from two games
